The paper proposes a novel approach for estimating energy bounds in embedded systems, which involves dividing a program into basic blocks and using evolutionary algorithms to establish maximal and minimal energy consumption for each block. This suggests that the paper could belong to the sub-categories of cs.AR (Hardware Architecture), cs.EM (Embedded Systems), cs.SY (Systems and Control), cs.PL (Programming Languages), or cs.SE (Software Engineering). Among these, cs.AR and cs.EM are the most likely categories, as the paper deals specifically with energy optimization and verification in embedded systems.
